<D>__{you live with fear, in the grip of fear fear of storms, fear of sickness on board, fear of the immensity. what if you never escape? how can you escape? there's nowhere to go. so you must drive your fear down, deep into your belly, and study your charts, and watch your compass, and pray for a fair wind and hope.}
